                     <interp inst="t18191027-73-person855" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191027-73-person855" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I fetched 
               <persName id="t18191027-73-person856">
                  Caroline 
                  Harris
               <interp inst="t18191027-73-person856" type="surname" value="Harris"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191027-73-person856" type="given" value="Caroline"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191027-73-person856" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             to my brother's - she lodged at my house - I returned home. Soon afterwards she came, and said she had lost her watch; I returned to my brother's with her and found the prisoner there. I got Pepper. I was in the shop, the prisoner stood by the cutting-board. I was left alone with her, and told her it was evident she had it, and if she gave it up it would be better. She fell on her knees, and begged I would do what I could for her - she picked it up from behind the chest and gave it to me. I called my brother and Harris up - Harris claimed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191027-73-person857">
                  CAROLINE 
                  HARRIS
               <interp inst="t18191027-73-person857" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
